            "source": "Benzinga",
            "category": "securities",
            "url": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/05/45581369/frontline-gears-up-for-q1-print-here-are-the-recent-forecast-changes-from-wall-streets-most-accurate-analysts",
            "summary": "Frontline plc (NYSE: FRO) is set to announce its first-quarter earnings on May 23. Analysts predict earnings of 23 cents per share, a decrease from 62 cents per share last year. Revenue for the quarter is expected to be around $264.19 million, down from $556.03 million in the previous year. In the fourth quarter, the company saw a 6.9% revenue growth year-over-year to $443.491 million, beating the consensus of $300.67 million. Frontline's shares closed at $17.18, a 2.9% decrease. For more details and analyst ratings, visit the full article on Benzinga.com.",
            "source_type": "news",
            "headline": "Frontline plc (NYSE: FRO) to release Q1 earnings on May 23 with expected EPS of 23 cents, down from 62 cents YoY. Revenue forecasted at $264.19 million, a significant decrease from $556.03 million YoY. Q4 revenue grew by 6.9% YoY to $443.491 million. Frontline shares closed at $17.18, dropping by 2.9%.",
            "tickers": [
