            "url": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/25/05/45581297/trumps-big-beautiful-3-8-trillion-bill-squeaks-through-house-expert-says-it-will-boost-the-economy-in-the-sh",
            "summary": "The $3.8 trillion tax-and-spending package proposed by President Donald Trump was narrowly approved by the U.S. House of Representatives with a slim margin of 215-214. The move caused a stir in bond markets, leading to a spike in 30-year Treasury yields to 5.15%, the highest level seen since October 2023. The bill, dubbed by Trump as his \"big, beautiful\" tax bill, is now on its way to the Senate for approval before the July 4 recess. While the package includes immediate economic stimulus measures such as widespread tax reductions and increased defense spending, experts are cautioning about potential long-term fiscal impacts. Jed Ellerbroek, a portfolio manager at Argent Capital Management, remarked on the bill's implications, noting that it lowers taxes for many and ramps up spending particularly in defense. For more details, visit Benzinga.com.",
            "source_type": "news",
            "headline": "Trump's $3.8 trillion bill narrowly passed House by 215-214 margin. Experts expect short-term boost but warn of worsening deficits. Bond markets react with 30-year Treasury yields spiking to 5.15%, highest level since October 2023. Bill heads to Senate for approval before July 4 recess.\u7a0ecuts, increased defense spending promised for short-term stimulus, but analysts warn of long-term fiscal consequences. Portfolio manager at Argent Capital Management states it reduces taxes for many & increases spending on defense.",
